a californian dream loan is for undergraduate students with exceptional financial need. the interest rate corresponds with the interest rate on the federal direct subsidized loans and is subject to change for new loans annually. the ca dream loan does not accrue interest while you are enrolled at least half-time, during periods of approved deferment, and during the 6-month grace period before you enter repayment. you will be responsible for the interest charged at all other times. for more information on the ca dream loan please see california dream act (ab540) http://www.sjsu.edu/faso/applying/californiadreamact/index.html please do not attempt to esign your promissory note or borrower information sheet until you receive notification from ecsi (educational computer systems, inc.) advising you to do so.notifications from ecsi will begin after july 1, 2018 for the 2018-2019 award year.ecsi, our billing servicer, will notify sjsu when you complete this process so your ca dream loan can be reviewed for disbursement to your student account. if you have any questions, please contact the bursar's office at bursar@sjsu.edu or at 408-924-1601.to maintain your loan via the web, contact sjsu billing agent,educational computer systems, inc. (ecsi). use this website to complete your required student loan.please contact your account specialist collections with any questions regarding your ca dream loan.phone:408-924-1601 monday - friday 9:00 a.m. - 4:00 p.m.live chat:mondays and wednesdays 1:00 - 3:00 p.m.tuesdays and thursdays 7:30 - 10:00 a.m.fridays 9:00 am - 12:00 noon email:bursar@sjsu.edu response time is one to three business days.deposits can be placed in the depository box at the student services center and is located to the right of the main doors.begin comm100 live chat code student services center 9th and san fernando st san jose, ca 95192-0138 to talk to a bursars office staff member in person,online you can choose to be notified by text as your turn approaches.monday - thursday 8:15 a.m. - 4:30 p.m.friday 9:00 a.m. - 4:30 p.m.